Social-distance bicycle riding is OK. It’s just as OK as solo walking, hiking or jogging.
For cycling in San Francisco, it’s hard to beat the 10-mile loop that starts at Stern Grove and includes the zoo, beach and Golden Gate Park.
A mile west, and all downhill, is the San Francisco Zoo.
The bison and the festival, two noble San Francisco institutions, will go on.
Steve Rubenstein is a San Francisco Chronicle staff writer.